{"key":"processedPost-16164653","value":{"id":16164653,"first":16164562,"last":16164761,"when":1335886304,"utime":"05/01/12 06:31 PM","cleanedPost":"Jars are very lame for agar.&nbsp; They take up ten or more times the space of a petri dish, and are deep which prevents CO2 from being expelled properly.&nbsp; They also cost ten times as much.&nbsp; If you're going to do agar, it soon becomes apparent that you'll have 50 or more plates going for a single strain isolation, and that's a LOT of jars.&nbsp; Use petri dishes, and the disposable are the way to go.<br />RR"}}